  <div id="change-84112" class="journal has-notes">
    <div id="note-4">
    <h4><a href="/issues/18494#note-4" class="journal-link">#4</a>
    <img alt="" class="gravatar" default="" rating="PG" src="http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1889ecb3526b191ac03f339073fe417f?rating=PG&amp;size=24&amp;default=" ssl="false" title="" />
    Updated by <a href="/users/1032" class="user active">Ken Barber</a> <a href="/projects/puppet/activity?from=2013-02-27" title="02/27/2013 09:59 am">6 months</a> ago</h4>

    <div class="wiki" id="journal-84112-notes"><p>For the purposes of Errata/Support &ndash; if you see an error like this in 3.1.0:</p>

<pre>
Error: Could not autoload puppet/type/firewall: constant Puppet::Type::Firewall not defined
Error: Could not autoload puppet/type/firewall: constant Puppet::Type::Firewall not defined on node box.bob.sh
Error: Could not autoload puppet/type/firewall: constant Puppet::Type::Firewall not defined on node box.bob.sh
</pre>


<p>For any type that is in a module, this patch probably fixes it.</p>

<p>We are specifically seeing this in Travis-CI tests for most of the puppetlabs modules.</p>
</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
